    <item>
      <title>Host static contents with Github Pages</title>
      <link>/blog/posts/host-static-contents-on-github-pages/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Oct 2016 20:10:12 +0900</pubDate>
      
      <guid>/blog/posts/host-static-contents-on-github-pages/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://pages.github.com/&#34;&gt;Github Pages&lt;/a&gt;  is a static site hosting service designed to host your personal, organization, or project pages directly from a GitHub repository.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However from repository settings / Github Pages, only master, master/doc option can be selected.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Actually there is another way to quickly host your repo&amp;rsquo;s static content with command line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Create a &lt;code&gt;gh-pages&lt;/code&gt; branch, push your static contents to this branch. fire up a browser then open &lt;code&gt;http://username.github.com/repo&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre style=&#34;;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4&#34;&gt;git checkout --orphan gh-pages  
git reset --hard
echo hello github pages &amp;gt; index.html
git commit -am &amp;#34;create index.html&amp;#34;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;when working with hugo, it&amp;rsquo;s really helpful to create a little script for deploy contents from &lt;code&gt;./public&lt;/code&gt; generated by &lt;code&gt;hugo&lt;/code&gt; command&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/hosting-and-deployment/hosting-on-github/#deployment-of-project-pages-from-your-gh-pages-branch&#34;&gt;read more details on hugo documentation&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
    </item>
    
